    AutoCloseable, Parallelizable, Panicable, Step<RelationshipRecord[]>
    public class ProcessRelationshipCountsDataStep
extends RecordProcessorStep<RelationshipRecord>
    Processes relationship records, feeding them to RelationshipCountsProcessor which keeps the accumulated counts per thread. Aggregated in RecordProcessorStep.done().

    • Method Detail

      • numberOfProcessors

        private static int numberOfProcessors​(Configuration config,
                                      NodeLabelsCache cache,
                                      int highLabelId,
                                      int highRelationshipTypeId)
        Keeping all counts for all combinations of label/reltype can require a lot of memory if there are lots of those tokens. Each processor will allocate such a data structure and so in extreme cases the number of processors will have to be limited to not surpass the available memory limits.
        Parameters:
        config - Configuration holding things like max number of processors and max memory.
        cache - NodeLabelsCache which is the only other data structure occupying memory at this point.
        highLabelId - high label id for this store.
        highRelationshipTypeId - high relationship type id for this store.
        Returns:
        number of processors suitable for this step. In most cases this will be 0, which is the typical value used when just allowing the importer to grab up to Configuration.maxNumberOfProcessors(). The returned value will at least be 1.
